# API base URL (optional in dev)
# - Physical phone: NEVER use localhost here — the phone is "localhost", not your PC.
#   Omit this line to auto-use the same LAN host as Metro (Expo), OR set explicitly:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.10:3001   (your PC's IPv4 from ipconfig / ifconfig)
# - Web / iOS Simulator on same Mac: http://localhost:3001 is OK if you uncomment it.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001

# If Expo Go shows "could not connect to the server" to Metro (not the API), try one of:
# 1) npm run dev:tunnel   (needs internet; works through guest Wi‑Fi / AP isolation)
# 2) Same Wi‑Fi as the PC; allow Node.js through Windows Defender Firewall (Private networks, ports 8081, 8082).
# 3) Force the packager URL host (QR code / deep link):
# REACT_NATIVE_PACKAGER_HOSTNAME=192.168.1.10
